Hi Adriene and the YWA community.  I have just completed the 30 Day Dedicate journey and I cried with pure joy on completion, it was so positively and beautifully emotional.  Wow, you are so amazing Adriene.  You bring out the best in all of us and I'm so grateful.  I've only been doing yoga for 7-8 weeks since I discovered you on You Tube. Through the incredible Dedicate journey I have learned so much about myself and my abilities, not just with regard to strength but in all areas of my life. Ive always been upbeat and positive and have practised and read self development books for 20 years or more but this yoga journey has somehow connected everything. It's as though I have woken up, I feel so alive, and it's all thanks to you for giving all these wonderful teachings for free. Thank you seems inadequate but thank you so much.  This must be your life's purpose Adriene and the light in you shines very brightly indeed.   My life is now moving in a new and  exciting  albeit a little scary direction, but yoga and your teachings have shown me that it's ok, I can deal with it. Thank you from the bottom of my heart.  Namaste

Hey, Adriene! Today I decided that when I start college, I will be doing  this to go with it. I'm a teenager who has battled with self esteem issues my whole life, and makeup is something I run to, scared. It's gotten to the point where my body quite literally is physically tight and stressed when I wear makeup. When I take it off, every time, the tension leaves my body.

I'm sick and tired of feeling like I can't be pretty without makeup, and I'm sure I've developed a little facial dysphoria because of it. 

So I saw this, and I saw that people are having their lives and mentalities and self images transformed and basically reborn. I really really want that. In fact, I *need* that.  So I'm doing it, and I'm not gonna wear makeup the entire month. I am so so scared just typing that. 

Wish me luck! I love you :)

I do weightlifting and cardio 3 times a week, and then practice your videos on my rest days. I feel much more aware--and in control--of what's going on with my body during weightlifting, I have better control over my breathing, and I'm much more balanced. Dear Adriene, i joined all your 30days journeys and i love them and i love you and honour you for the way you embody feminine leadership! There is one thing missing for me tough, which is menstrual cycle awareness. Most of your followers are women, and your yoga journeys are exactly 30 days, meaning women who experience their cycle regularly, will bleed during this journey. It would be wonderful and a great gift for womankind, if you would mention this and bring awareness to it, and mention that during our bleeding time and the 1,2 days before, we should take a gentle practice, no bandhas, no inversions, a day of total rest or yoga nidra day one of the cycle, allowing a day or more of break from the journey etc. We are trained to function, work etc 365 days a year, wheter we're bleeding or not. I think in the yoga world thats a big problem and it needs to be adressed that women shouldn't do vigorous yoga practice 30 days a month, that can harm our bodies and minds seriously.
So, i would be grateful if you use your wonderful voice to bring awareness to this, or who knows, maybe the 30days journey 2020 is designed cyclical... lots of love to you, thanks for shining your light :-)
